1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,000
We have learned to use and group blocks to build our site.

2
00:00:04,000 --> 00:00:07,000
But do you know there is a shortcut to create custom content layouts faster,

3
00:00:09,000 --> 00:00:12,000
and that is using block patterns.

4
00:00:12,000 --> 00:00:15,000
We are not all designers and it is time consuming to create layouts.

5
00:00:16,000 --> 00:00:19,000
Block patterns provide a solution.

6
00:00:19,000 --> 00:00:22,000
The learning objectives for this lesson are using and modifying available pre-made block patterns,

7
00:00:25,000 --> 00:00:28,000
exploring the Block Pattern Directory, creating your own synced and non-synced patterns,

8
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:33,000
and lastly utilizing header and footer patterns.

9
00:00:34,000 --> 00:00:37,000
But what are patterns?

10
00:00:36,000 --> 00:00:39,000
Block patterns are pre-made designs or layouts of grouped blocks that are available to modify and change to meet your needs.

11
00:00:43,000 --> 00:00:46,000
It will essentially save you time, but also enhance creativity and design.

12
00:00:48,000 --> 00:00:51,000
Instead of nesting and grouping blocks together, patterns have already done that for you.

13
00:00:53,000 --> 00:00:56,000
And in one click you will have access to beautiful and functional layouts from call to actions, headers, columns, galleries and more.

14
00:01:02,000 --> 00:01:05,000
To add a pattern, click on the plus icon on the top left, also called the Inserter,

15
00:01:08,000 --> 00:01:11,000
and open up the patterns tab on the right next to Blocks.

16
00:01:12,000 --> 00:01:15,000
At the top you will see all patterns.

17
00:01:15,000 --> 00:01:18,000
And below that all your synced and non-synced patterns you have created yourself.

18
00:01:21,000 --> 00:01:24,000
Synced patterns are marked with a purple icon and non-synced patterns don't have one,

19
00:01:26,000 --> 00:01:29,000
but more about synced and non-synced patterns in a moment.

20
00:01:30,000 --> 00:01:33,000
Below My patterns you will see the patterns that come with your theme.

21
00:01:34,000 --> 00:01:37,000
They are organized into various categories to help you find what you need.

22
00:01:39,000 --> 00:01:42,000
Once you click on the category you will see a preview of all the available patterns when you scroll down.

23
00:01:46,000 --> 00:01:49,000
You can also select Explore All Patterns at the bottom to get a bird's eye view of the patterns that come with your theme.

24
00:01:54,000 --> 00:01:57,000
You can also go through them category by category.

25
00:01:59,000 --> 00:02:02,000
Let's look at a quick example.

26
00:02:02,000 --> 00:02:05,000
When you select a pattern, in this case one from my Featured category, you will be able to modify the pattern to meet your design requirements.

27
00:02:10,000 --> 00:02:13,000
It can easily be edited in the same way as any other block.

28
00:02:15,000 --> 00:02:18,000
You can change the alignment of the container block.

29
00:02:19,000 --> 00:02:22,000
You can edit the heading, update the content, replace the images,

30
00:02:33,000 --> 00:02:36,000
and for example change the background color of your pattern as well as other styling options.

31
00:02:40,000 --> 00:02:43,000
But all the hard work and the layout has already been done for you.

32
00:02:44,000 --> 00:02:47,000
The only thing you have to do is select the pattern and modify it to meet your requirements.

33
00:02:51,000 --> 00:02:54,000
The patterns that come with your theme are limited.

34
00:02:54,000 --> 00:02:57,000
If you want more patterns to choose from, you can explore the Block Pattern Directory.

35
00:02:59,000 --> 00:03:02,000
To do that, let's make our way to the WordPress.org website.

36
00:03:04,000 --> 00:03:07,000
Click on "Extend" and then select "Patterns".

37
00:03:10,000 --> 00:03:13,000
Here you can search and find new patterns to use on your website.

38
00:03:15,000 --> 00:03:18,000
You will notice there is an option to only view curated patterns or hundreds of patterns that have been added by the WordPress community.

39
00:03:24,000 --> 00:03:27,000
You can type in the search block, search by category, or browse through all the available options until you find what you're looking for.

40
00:03:33,000 --> 00:03:36,000
Once you find the pattern you are after, you can click on the "Star" to add it to your favorites.

41
00:03:39,000 --> 00:03:42,000
When you are ready to add the pattern to your site, open the pattern, click on "Copy Pattern", return to your website, and then paste.

42
00:03:54,000 --> 00:03:57,000
And now you can start changing and modifying your pattern.

43
00:04:00,000 --> 00:04:03,000
And this is what my pattern looks like after altering it to meet my design needs.

44
00:04:06,000 --> 00:04:09,000
When you make your way to the Site Editor

45
00:04:10,000 --> 00:04:13,000
and in the Side View you will see a Patterns tab.

46
00:04:14,000 --> 00:04:17,000
And here you can manage, edit, and create all of your patterns, synced or not, along with your template parts.

47
00:04:22,000 --> 00:04:25,000
When you click on "My Patterns", you will see all your custom patterns.

48
00:04:26,000 --> 00:04:29,000
The synced patterns have a purple icon and the unsynced patterns don't.

49
00:04:31,000 --> 00:04:34,000
If you hover over the purple icon, it clearly says, "Editing this pattern will also update anywhere it is used".

50
00:04:39,000 --> 00:04:42,000
Below custom patterns, we will see all the available categories as well as the patterns that are provided by your theme.

51
00:04:47,000 --> 00:04:50,000
It is also worth noting, when you click on the three vertical dots of a pattern that comes with your theme, you can also duplicate and

52
00:04:55,000 --> 00:04:58,000
add that pattern to your custom patterns area, and when you've saved it as a custom pattern you can modify it as you please.

53
00:05:02,000 --> 00:05:05,000
And at the bottom, all your header, footer, and general template part patterns.

54
00:05:08,000 --> 00:05:11,000
Let's start with your own patterns.

55
00:05:11,000 --> 00:05:14,000
If you click on the plus icon next to "Patterns", you can create your own custom synced or unsynced patterns.

56
00:05:18,000 --> 00:05:21,000
After naming it, you can add it to the relevant category, in this case, "Call to Action" category, and then you can choose to sync it or not.

57
00:05:31,000 --> 00:05:34,000
In this example, I will choose to sync the pattern, and at the bottom, it says, "Sync this pattern across multiple locations".

58
00:05:41,000 --> 00:05:44,000
And now you can start creating your synced pattern, and when it is ready, we can click "Save".

59
00:05:49,000 --> 00:05:52,000
To create a pattern in the block editor, merely select the design, then click on the three vertical dots of the block toolbar, and select "Create Pattern".

60
00:06:02,000 --> 00:06:05,000
And then follow the same process as before, and I will once again select a synced pattern.

61
00:06:12,000 --> 00:06:15,000
So, if you love a design, you can save it and reuse it as a synced or non-synced pattern.

62
00:06:18,000 --> 00:06:21,000
Lastly, let's talk about template parts.

63
00:06:21,000 --> 00:06:24,000
To manage your header and footer, you have template part patterns at your disposal.

64
00:06:26,000 --> 00:06:29,000
Templates create a design for a webpage, and this is usually done by adding a header and footer template part.

65
00:06:32,000 --> 00:06:35,000
Let's look at an example and open up our page template.

66
00:06:38,000 --> 00:06:41,000
And when you open your page template, we can go ahead and select our current header, and then click on the three vertical dots.

67
00:06:48,000 --> 00:06:51,000
And now we can select "Replace Header".

68
00:06:51,000 --> 00:06:54,000
And when you do this, you can select one of your existing template parts or patterns that come with your theme.

69
00:06:58,000 --> 00:07:01,000
And it works exactly the same way with your footer.

70
00:07:02,000 --> 00:07:05,000
Below patterns, you can manage and edit your existing template parts.

71
00:07:09,000 --> 00:07:12,000
To add a new template part, click on the plus icon next to "Patterns" and select "Create Template Part".

72
00:07:15,000 --> 00:07:18,000
Here you will be able to select between creating a general, footer or header template part.

73
00:07:22,000 --> 00:07:25,000
To create a new header template part, name it appropriately, select "Header" and then click "Create".

74
00:07:30,000 --> 00:07:33,000
And then you can start building your new header in template editing mode.

75
00:07:36,000 --> 00:07:39,000
I trust that patterns will also become one of your favorite new tools.

